                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                <head>No. 343.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Edward Thornton</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-06-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 9, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of yesterday’s date respecting the expediency of so modifying the
                    rules regulating the importation of cattle into Canada as to permit short-horned
                    cattle raised west of the Alleghany Mountains to enter the Dominion of Canada
                    unobstructed, for breeding purposes.</p>
                <p>I am forwarding a copy of your note to the governor-general of the Dominion, with
                    a request that the attention of the Canadian Government may be invited to this
                    important subject, and I shall also transmit a copy of it to Earl Granville.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EDW’D THORNTON.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
